hhvm (2.4.1-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [ David Martínez Moreno ]
  * Initial release (closes: #727085).
  * Version released on 2014-02-13.
  * debian/rules: Build the package with --as-needed to remove a couple of
    bogus dependencies,
  * debian/patches:
    - 01_fix_freetype_include: Bad include in libgd.
    - 02_use_system_libzip: Add CMake code to use the system's libzip.
    - 06_typos: Lots of typos, most of them detected by lintian. Added the
      false positives to a lintian override file.
    - 07_disable_vpx_in_libgd: Disable VPx code in libgd to make sure we don't
      get an additional dependency if it's present in the system.
    - 08_disable_libncurses: Disable libncurses CMake and linking code.
    - 09_remove_boost_regex_hhvm: Disable boost_regex in CMake code.
    - 10_remove_libpam: Disable libpam CMake and linking code.

  [ Faidon Liambotis ]
  * debian/patches:
    - 03_prefer_libedit_over_libreadline: workaround build system bug
      and prefer libedit over libreadline.
    - 04_generated_files_prebuild: allow generated_files.sh to be run
      before HHVM is built to run it for DFSG completeness reasons.
    - 05_bison3_whitespace: Change to the whitespace matching to support
      both Bison 2 and 3.

 -- David Martínez Moreno <ender@debian.org>  Wed, 12 Mar 2014 15:31:34 -0700
